Batch script:

```batch
@echo off

set FILE=Deathlist.csv
set DATE_COLUMN=Date of death
set OUT_PLOT=weekly_deaths.png

:: Read dataset and process date field
python -c "import pandas as pd; from datetime import timedelta; df = pd.read_csv('%FILE%'); 
        df['week'] = (df[df%DATE COLUMN%) / 1e9).dt.week + 1; print(df.to_string(index=False))" > deathlist.txt

:: Create histogram
python -c "import pandas as pd; from matplotlib import pyplot as plt; df = pd.read_csv('deathlist.txt');
        df['week'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar'); plt.xlabel('Week'); plt.ylabel('Count of Deaths');
        plt.title('Weekly Deaths Distribution'); plt.savefig('%OUT_PLOT%')" > histogram.ps

:: Clean up
echo.
del deathlist.txt /Q
```

Note: Please make sure you have python and matplotlib installed on your system. Also, the script assumes that the data in "Date of death" field is in Unix timestamp format (integer number of seconds since 1/1/1970). If not, please adjust the batch script accordingly.
